 The 24th American Music Awards, one of the biggest music events of the year, will be telecast live on Wednesday at 6. 30 am on STAR World. Twenty awards will be given out representing the best of Pop/Rock, Country, Soul/Rhythm amp; Blues, Rap/Hip Hop, Latin, Alternative, Adult Contemporary and Contemporary Inspirational music.

 Mariah Carey, the Red Hot Chili Peppers, The Black Eyed Peas and Nickelback lead the nominations with three nods each. Carey, a nine-time American Music Award winner, has been nominated for Favourite Female Artist in both the Pop/Rock and Soul/Rhythm amp; Blues categories, as well as Favourite Album in the Soul/Rhythm amp; Blues category for The Emancipation of Mimi.

 The 2006 American Music Awards will be hosted by Jimmy Kimmel and will be beamed from the Shrine Auditorium in Los Angeles.

 Performers announced for the ceremony thus far are Beyonce, Carrie Underwood, Dixie Chicks, Gwen Stefani, Josh Groban, Mary J. Blige, Nelly Furtado, Pussycat Dolls, Rascal Flatts, Snow Patrol and Tenacious D.

 If you are dont manage to get up so early, there is a prime-time repeat telecast of the American Music Awards at 8 pm on STAR World.

